# P4 Implementation: CAP_CUSTOM_WASM_URL 时序竞态治本

## Changed Files

### 1. frontend-v3/src/main.ts

**Change**: Added `window.CAP_CUSTOM_WASM_URL` assignment after imports, before `createApp`.

**Diff**:
```diff
 import './styles/base.css'
 
+// CAP_CUSTOM_WASM_URL must be set before @cap.js/widget is loaded.
+// cap.js reads this at module-evaluation time to determine WASM fetch URL.
+// This works because @cap.js/widget is only imported inside LoginDialog.vue,
+// which is lazy-loaded via router — so cap.js loads AFTER main.ts executes.
+window.CAP_CUSTOM_WASM_URL = '/wasm/cap_wasm_bg.wasm'
+
 const app = createApp(App)
```

**Rationale**: Moves the WASM URL assignment from index.html inline script into the JS module graph. Since `@cap.js/widget` is only reachable via lazy-loaded route chunks, main.ts's module body executes before cap.js is ever loaded.

### 2. frontend-v3/index.html

**Change**: Removed CAP_CUSTOM_WASM_URL inline script and its comment.

**Diff**:
```diff
     <script src="/js/theme-init.js"></script>
-    <!-- Captcha WASM local path (must be set before Vue loads) -->
-    <script>window.CAP_CUSTOM_WASM_URL = '/wasm/cap_wasm_bg.wasm'</script>
     <!-- GitHub Markdown CSS (local) -->
```

**Rationale**: Single source of truth — the variable is now only set in main.ts, eliminating the risk of maintaining two locations for the same setting.

### 3. frontend-v3/src/vite-env.d.ts (NEW)

**Change**: Created Vite environment type declaration file with Window extension for `CAP_CUSTOM_WASM_URL`.

**Content**:
```typescript
/// <reference types="vite/client" />

declare global {
  interface Window {
    CAP_CUSTOM_WASM_URL?: string
  }
}

export {}
```

**Rationale**: Moving the `window.CAP_CUSTOM_WASM_URL` assignment from plain JS (index.html) to TypeScript (main.ts) requires a type declaration. This is the standard Vite project convention.

